      "TradeItemDescriptionModule": {
        "TradeItemDescriptionInformation": {
          "AdditionalTradeItemDescription": [
            {
              "LanguageCode": "en",
              "Value": "Chemiluminescence Immunoassay Analyzer performs complete sample processing (sample pre-dilutions, sample and reagent dispensing, incubations, wash processes, etc.) as well as measurement and evaluation to improve efficiency in the immunoassay laboratories. It adopts chemiluminescence immunoassay technology (CLIA) with paramagnetic microparticle solid phase.\nChemiluminescence is the emission of light (luminescence) that  is emitted by a substance when it returns from an excited state to a ground state, as the result of a chemical reaction. An immunoassay is a biochemical test that measures the presence or concentration of a macromolecule or a small molecule in a solution through the use of an antibody or immunoglobulin. CLIA, combining chemiluminescence with immunoassay, is ultra-sensitive and can detect small amounts of the biological molecule. In addition to this, it has a wider dynamic range, as well as having a linear relationship between luminous intensity and the concentration of the measured substance."
            }
          ],
